reviewText: This movie was horrible, I hate to ruin the film, but if I can save someone some money than it is worth it, because I am ready 2 give this movie, back or throw in the trash. The movie follows 3 couples who get married at the same time all the husbands are bus drivers , so the husbands all start cheating, one husband meets and falls in love with a young woman whom he later finds out is hooker, and then when a trick beats her, she goes to the hospital, an d it is revealed she has HIV,the husband then finds out he has HIV, so he goes home to tell his wife shoot and kill himself,the next husband decides to cheat on his wife who happens to be a cop with  a white woman, his wife the cop bust him in illegal gambling ring, but she discovers the affair cause the white girl is there,so he lies to the wife, she forgives him, but warns him, he lies to the white girl she gives him another chance, so the wife is at work she goes home early,and finds her husband with the white woman having sex so she shoots him, and her killing them both. The third husband does not cheat but has a wife that only cares about her looks, and money so he meets an overweight woman, and he leaves his wife for her, and it turns out his wife is a lesbian, that is why she stopped having sex with him, but then and this is the kicker, it shows him waking up in bed with the woman we think is the one he left his wife for, but lo and behold it is his wife, and comes to find out he was dreaming, and the movie is over??????REALLY???? so did he dream everything????or just the part about him leaving his wife???? You can buy this movie if u want but I promise u will be upset, there are people that gave this movie high ranks, but I would not want this movie for free, it ends stupid so u really do not know what was real, or dream and then it ends...WORST MONEY I HAVE SPENT I TRULY COULD HAVE HAD A V-8 IT WOULD HAVE BEEN BETTER AND WORTH THE MONEY THAN THIS FILM!!!!!

reviewText: This movie was made with $50 and a biscuit. I kept rooting for it to improve but it just got worse and worse. Horrible. If I made this movie and watched the final cut I would have thought...hmmmm I respect cinema too much to EVER put this out in the public. Obviously that was not the case with these film makers. It was so sucky that I felt like I should have been paid for being able to watch 85% of it before deciding I liked myself more and turned it off.  Yuk.

reviewText: The message in this film very clear and goes on in the world today. Why marry if you don't keep YOUR VOW TO GOD SACRED? What you do in the dark will come to light. If a person is changing you and not for the better why do you feel the need to stay. Sometimes the things you pray to keep together God is trying to move you from it. BE CAREFUL WHAT YOU PRAY FOR & RECOGNIZE YOUR BLESSINGS. The ending sucked and could have been better. On a scale of 1-10 this movie gets a 6.

reviewText: The movie here you'll feel good about adding it to your collection... The three married co-workers have to decide whether they're happy with the circumstances or path their marriages have taken... The budget wasn't hollywood, No major stars but this Texas crew pulled it out with a product worth selling... Though you gotta feel sorry for a guy who shares a bed with his five kids and his wife(who's a cop)... Men in relationships before marriage ask themselves all the time "Do I want to subject myself to this or that person under those circumstances or issue".., Outside of their marriages these co-workers felt they had the same options...
